The wave doesn't cause the rotation, that remains
from the angular momentum of the material that
formed the galaxy. The wave moves round the galaxy
and can move in the opposite direction to the
rotation. Throw a pebble in a stream and ripples
can move upstream as well as down.

I can't help with what causes the difference, I
think that is still being studied.

